          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1635258042388-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1635258042388-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is browning, peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Once browned, transfer the<strong> browned chicken</strong> to a plate, reserve the pan and juices</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [3 1/2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and cook for 5-8 min or until soft and starting to caramelise</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1635258047506-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
